setRepeatConditions

void setRepeatConditions(java.lang.String conditions)
                   throws GrammarException
Sets the mininum and maximum number of repetitions

Parameters:
conditions - The two possibilities are: "n" -> Repeated exactly n times "m-n" -> Repeated between m and n times (both extremes included)
Throws:
GrammarException - When the repeat condition cannot be parsed
